docs.abstract: A presidential executive order banning the “malign ideology” of racial sensitivity training has rippled through government into academia and corporate America.
docs.snippet: A presidential executive order banning the “malign ideology” of racial sensitivity training has rippled through government into academia and corporate America.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — For the diversity consulting industry, this summer was like no other. Amid the racial reckoning spurred by the death of George Floyd, a wave of senior-level executives began to look critically at their companies, and consultants like Melanie Miller and Loretta VanPelt found themselves deluged with work.

headline.main: Trump Attack on Diversity Training Has a Quick and Chilling Effect

docs.abstract: African-Americans know what it feels like to be ignored by those in power. Thanks to Trump, the rest of America is getting a taste of that now.
docs.snippet: African-Americans know what it feels like to be ignored by those in power. Thanks to Trump, the rest of America is getting a taste of that now.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — During President Trump’s fund-raising trip to Beverly Hills, Calif., this month — the first time he’d come to the official state of resistance since becoming president — a couple of friends of mine took to the streets, along with hundreds of others, to protest. But the visit was highly stage-managed, and Mr. Trump never faced the crowd; the most my friends could do, they said, was raise a middle finger to the sky as his aircraft flew overhead.

docs.abstract: Keenan Scott II’s play, incorporating slam poetry, prose and songs, aspires to be a lyrical reckoning with Black life in America.
docs.snippet: Keenan Scott II’s play, incorporating slam poetry, prose and songs, aspires to be a lyrical reckoning with Black life in America.
docs.lead_paragraph: Seven Black men step onto the stage in the opening of Keenan Scott II’s “Thoughts of a Colored Man.” Over the course of the play, each will reveal a personality and history, but not a name, though later they will introduce themselves as Love, Happiness, Wisdom, Lust, Passion, Depression and Anger. Wearing different combinations of black, gray and red, they stand staring at a hulking billboard that reads “COLORED” in declarative black caps.

headline.main: Review: ‘Thoughts of a Colored Man’ Preaches to the Choir
headline.print_headline: What’s It Like Being Black? Let Them Tell You.

docs.abstract: Seeing depictions of women who mentor and rely on one another with such fierce loyalty is still a rarity on TV.
docs.snippet: Seeing depictions of women who mentor and rely on one another with such fierce loyalty is still a rarity on TV.
docs.lead_paragraph: On the surface, “The Good Fight” has much in common with its predecessor, “The Good Wife.” The power plays among Chicago’s elite lawyers lend the series a bracing wit. Role reversals happen with breakneck speed. Clothing informs characterization as much as dialogue does. There are, of course, familiar faces and names. Occasionally Alicia Florrick, the prickly lead of the original series, is mentioned in passing. But “The Good Fight” stands on its own because of the way it traffics in the thorny dynamics that arise among women who are navigating professional minefields, complex desires and identity politics. The way these women relate to each other as colleagues, lovers and friends powers the entire show.

headline.main: ‘The Good Fight’ Recap: On the Other Side

docs.abstract: He is the only African-American driver in NASCAR’s top-flight racing series, and this week got the organization to bar the Confederate flag at its events.
docs.snippet: He is the only African-American driver in NASCAR’s top-flight racing series, and this week got the organization to bar the Confederate flag at its events.
docs.lead_paragraph: Bubba Wallace, who instigated NASCAR’s banning of the Confederate flag, is the racing series’ only black driver. That has put him in the spotlight in a sport whose owners, drivers, crews and fans have historically been predominantly white.

headline.print_headline: A Black Driver Steps Into the Spotlight
